  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dc4 \u0daf\u0dac\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dda\u0db1\u0dcf\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0db3\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Divide with two spoons for the elephant and the elephant",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Crop Damage Committee has focused on removing crop damaging animals from the list of protected animals.",
        "The committee has also decided not to remove the wild elephant from the list of protected animals even though it damages crops. Despite being the national animal, the Dadulena has been included in the list of endangered animals.",
        "At present, it has been recognized that 40 percent of the crops cultivated by Sri Lankan farmers are destroyed by animals every year and this situation has seriously affected the national food security.",
        "In the discussions held by the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forestry, Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera with all the farmer organizations regarding the reduction of crop damage by wild animals, the farmer representatives have stated that due to the destruction of crops by certain animals, they have become unable to get proper income.",
        "A committee was appointed by Minister Mahinda Amaraweera to look into the matter and the Secretary of the Ministry of Agriculture, Secretary of the Ministry of Wildlife and Forest Resources and Director General of Wildlife are members of the committee."
      ],
